This feedback identifies the finalized, production-ready implementation for replacing krdp (TCP) with Moonlight/Sunshine (UDP). This upgrade transitions the project from a "Remote Desktop" setup to a "Professional-Grade Gaming Cloud."

1. The Argument for the Upgrade: "Zero-Latency"

The legacy RDP approach relies on TCP, which causes "TCP Meltdown" (stuttering/freezing) during packet loss.

Performance: Sunshine/Moonlight uses UDP with VA-API (AMD/Intel) hardware encoding, providing a 1:1, 4K/60FPS feel indistinguishable from a local monitor.

Stealth Security: Using WireGuard (UDP) instead of SSH tunnels for video traffic is faster and more secure. WireGuard uses "Silent Drop," making your VPN port invisible to scanners.

Automation: By using official Docker images and host-level module loading, the setup remains compatible with Watchtower for 100% automated security updates.

2. Final Implementation: The "Golden Path"
Phase A: Host OS Preparation (Bazzite)

To support containerized VPN routing and hardware-accelerated streaming, run these on the server:

# 1. Load legacy NAT modules (required for wg-easy + Watchtower compatibility)
sudo modprobe iptable_nat iptable_mangle
echo -e "iptable_nat\niptable_mangle" | sudo tee /etc/modules-load.d/iptables-legacy.conf

# 2. Grant Hardware Permissions (Mouse/Keyboard/GPU)
sudo usermod -aG input,video,render $(whoami)
sudo ujust setup-sunshine

# 3. Enable Session Persistence (Starts Sunshine/Audio at boot)
sudo loginctl enable-linger $(whoami)
Phase B: The Stealth VPN (WireGuard)

Deploy wg-easy via Docker. This provides the secure "tunnel" into your home.

Router: Forward only port 51820/udp.

Server Firewall: Keep Sunshine ports open internally but never forward them on the router.

# docker-compose.yml for wg-easy
services:
  wg-easy:
    image: ghcr.io/wg-easy/wg-easy:latest
    container_name: wg-easy
    restart: unless-stopped
    labels: ["com.centurylinklabs.watchtower.enable=true"]
    environment:
      - WG_HOST=yourname.duckdns.org
      - PASSWORD_HASH=$$2a$$12$$... # Your Bcrypt hash
    volumes: ["./data:/etc/wireguard:Z"]
    ports:
      - "51820:51820/udp"
      - "127.0.0.1:51821:51821/tcp" # Admin UI (Internal only)
    cap_add: [NET_ADMIN, SYS_MODULE]
    sysctls:
      - net.ipv4.ip_forward=1
Phase C: The Streaming Layer (Sunshine)

Start Service: systemctl --user enable --now sunshine

Firewall: Open ports locally for the VPN to "see" them:
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port={47984,47989,48010}/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port={47998,47999,48000,48002,48010}/udp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload && sudo systemctl restart docker

3. New Remote Workflow (Client-Side)

This replaces the old RDP/SSH tunnel instructions.

Connect VPN: Use nmcli (Linux) or the WireGuard app to connect.

