Launch Session: SSH to trigger the graphical session:
ssh -p 22022 sotohome@jsotohome.duckdns.org 'sudo start-kde.sh'

Stream: Open Moonlight and connect to the server's VPN IP (10.8.0.1).

4. Critical Pitfalls to Include

Pitfall: User Permissions. Group changes (usermod) and enable-linger require a sudo loginctl terminate-user $(whoami) or a full reboot to take effect.

Pitfall: Dual Interfaces. Moonlight may struggle to find the server if the VPN is on. Always use the internal VPN IP (10.8.0.1) when connecting remotely.

Pitfall: Headless Output. A $5 HDMI Dummy Plug is mandatory for headless servers to "wake" the GPU for KDE sessions.
